  "title": "Clinic Assistant #77376",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Medical Clinic / General Practitioner</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Clinic Assistant</strong></li><li>Working Location: Woodlands</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + OT Pay + Variable Bonus + Medical Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Greet and register patients, manage appointment scheduling, and handle walk-ins efficiently.</li><li>Assist doctors during consultations and minor procedures.</li><li>Prepare consultation rooms, ensuring cleanliness and readiness before and after each patient.</li><li>Dispense medications accurately as prescribed, with proper labeling and instructions.</li><li>Manage payment collection and issue receipts; assist with claims and billing (e.g. Medisave, CHAS, insurance portals).</li><li>Maintain accurate patient records and update clinic management systems.</li><li>Perform basic clinical duties such as taking vitals (height, weight, blood pressure, etc.), if trained.</li><li>Manage clinic supplies, inventory, and stock replenishment.</li><li>Ensure a clean and safe environment in the clinic at all times.</li><li>Handle incoming calls and general inquiries professionally.</li><li>Provide administrative support and assist with any other ad hoc duties as required.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum GCE 'O' Level or relevant certificate in healthcare support or administration.</li><li>Candidates without relevant experience are welcome to apply. Training will be provided.</li><li>Able to multitask, work in a fast-paced environment, and handle patients with empathy and professionalism.</li><li>Basic knowledge of Microsoft Office and clinic management systems preferred.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#77376 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
